HEADWORD: Dacapo
<hw>Da`ca"po</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[It., from [the] head or
beginning.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>From the beginning; a direction
to return to, and end with, the first strain; -- indicated by the
letters <it>D. C.</it> Also, the strain so repeated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dace</ent>⟦br⟧
